ComposeAlertMessage.inputs:
Hi Team, 
Azure Netapp Files storage is low for @{triggerBody()?['netappAccount']}. Alerts for low storage will trigger when the consumed storage percentage of the ANF volume goes above 90% usage.

For more details please check below. 
AzureNetappAccount: @{triggerBody()?['netappAccount']}
VolumeName: @{triggerBody()?['Volume']}
ResourceGroup: @{triggerBody()?['ResourceGroup']}
ConsumedPercent: @{triggerBody()?['ConsumedPercent']}
SubscriptionName:@{body('Parse-GetTenantID')?['displayName']} 
SubscriptionId: @{triggerBody()?['SubscriptionId']}

Hi Team,

An Azure Netapp Files volume was detected without a Snapshot Policy for  @{triggerBody()?['netappAccount']}. All ANF Volumes should have a snapshot policy enabled.

For more details please check below. 
AzureNetappAccount: @{triggerBody()?['netappAccount']}
VolumeName: @{triggerBody()?['Volume']}
ResourceGroup: @{triggerBody()?['ResourceGroup']}
SubscriptionName:@{body('Parse-GetTenantID')?['displayName']} 
SubscriptionId: @{triggerBody()?['SubscriptionId']}
